         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... high, big. Like the jungle inhabitant ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... all (will be un)satisfied, the Gaṅgā river will become dry ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">and ... is ... Thereupon the Gaṅgā river ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... she [is] sitting apart ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... with non-greenness the venerable one [fem.] has burnt ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Which water they did not obtain to drink ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... O noble one, do not (forsake) the Pre(tas)! ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... you should give alms! The horrible Pretas ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I [fem.] will be without refuge. 1. ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I [f.] will be without refuge</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>630</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">because of ... we ... abandon(ing) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">because of these ones we are not worthy ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>46</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">this is the reason why these Pretas ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
